<paragraph blockId="8.[151,414,1736,1763]" box="[151,414,1736,1763]" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,414,1736,1763]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Robertson" authorityName="Robertson" box="[151,414,1736,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Peponapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,414,1736,1763]" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">Peponapis</emphasis>
Robertson
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1814,2034]" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">
The genus 
<emphasis box="[284,412,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">Poponapis</emphasis>
contains several species, which are distributed mostly in North and Central 
<collectingCountry box="[1333,1436,1814,1840]" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">America</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Urban" box="[159,373,1853,1879]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" refString="Urban, D., Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (2007) Eucerini Latreille, 1802. In Moure J. S., Urban D. &amp; G. A. R. Melo (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 167 - 213." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Urban 
<emphasis box="[242,294,1853,1878]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[309,373,1853,1879]" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). All species of the genus visit crops of 
<taxonomicName box="[845,964,1853,1878]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Cucurbita" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[845,964,1853,1878]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">Cucurbita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to obtain pollen (
<bibRefCitation author="Hurd" box="[1173,1431,1853,1879]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" refString="Hurd, P. D. &amp; Linsley, E. G. (1967) South American Squash and Gourd Bees of the Genus Peponapis (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 60, 647 - 661." type="journal article" year="1967">
Hurd &amp; Linsley 
<number box="[1369,1431,1853,1879]" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" value="1967.0">1967</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wagenknecht" box="[151,387,1892,1918]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" refString="Wagenknecht, R. (1970) Contribucion a la biologia de los Apoidea chilenos. Anales del Museo de Historia Natural, 3, 111 - 127." type="journal article" year="1970">
Wagenknecht 
<number box="[322,387,1892,1918]" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" value="1970.0">1970</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Some species are broadly distributed, due to the extension of cultivation of domestic 
<taxonomicName authority="Michener 2007" authorityName="Michener" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,488,1930,1956]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Cucurbita" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,272,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">Cucurbita</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Michener" box="[289,479,1930,1956]" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" refString="Michener, C. D. (2007) The bees of the world (2 Â° Ed.). John Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, xvi + 992 pp." type="book" year="2007">
Michener 
<number box="[414,479,1930,1956]" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The South American species of 
<taxonomicName box="[887,1013,1931,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Peponapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[887,1013,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">Peponapis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hurd" pageId="8" pageNumber="30" refString="Hurd, P. D. &amp; Linsley, E. G. (1967) South American Squash and Gourd Bees of the Genus Peponapis (Hymenoptera: Apoidea). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 60, 647 - 661." type="journal article" year="1967">
Hurd &amp; Linsley (
<number box="[160,224,1969,1995]" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" value="1967.0">1967</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. These autors also illustratrated some male structures of the species 
<taxonomicName box="[1036,1150,1969,1995]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Peponapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fervens">
<emphasis box="[1036,1050,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1066,1150,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">fervens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Friese" authorityName="Friese" box="[1166,1386,1969,1995]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Peponapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melonis">
<emphasis box="[1166,1181,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1196,1287,1969,1994]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">melonis</emphasis>
(Friese)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cockerell" authorityName="Cockerell" box="[151,432,2008,2034]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Peponapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrullina">
<emphasis box="[151,166,2008,2033]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[180,289,2008,2033]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">citrullina</emphasis>
(Cockerell)
</taxonomicName>
, the latter being the only species of 
<taxonomicName box="[854,978,2008,2033]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Peponapis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[854,978,2008,2033]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">Peponapis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represented in 
<collectingCountry box="[1157,1224,2008,2034]" name="Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="24">Chile</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
